Some notes
###########

#Easy server for testing: 
Run script/pageapp_server.pl to test the application while in the application dir.


#Cleaning session data:
A crontab job cleans up any old session data. Setup should be like this:
*/30 * * * * find /www/tmp/session/ -maxdepth 1 -type d -regex "/www/tmp/session/.+" -cmin +120 -exec rm -rf {} \;


#Git related
.gitattributes makes sure that diffs between dev and master branches dont get merged for the file 'pageapp.yaml'

#LIVE setup related:
Replace 172.17.200.84 with our public IP address in pageapp.psgi file.

#An example way to run this web app:
First, start starman webserver, listen to port 8001:
starman -I/www/www-dev/lib/ -I/www/perllib/lib/perl5 /www/www-dev/pageapp.psgi --pid /www/www-dev/log/starman.pid --port 8001 --error-log /www/www-dev/log/starman.error.log --access-log /www/www-dev/log/starman.access.log


Second, start reverse-proxy webserver, in this case nginx which will listen to 8000 and serve static contents. Everything else will be forwarded to starman at port 8001:
/www/nginx/local/nginx -p /www/nginx/local/ -c /www/www-dev/nginx.conf
